snippet: A Food and Drug Administration finding has given ammunition to consumer advocates who say the quality of generic drugs needs to be improved.
abstract: Food and Drug Administration will look more closely at how generic companies make extended release drugs following its investigation of Impax Laboratories, which produced defective version of common antidepressant Wellbutrin; finding is rare departure for FDA, which has long insisted that generics are as effective as their brand-name counterparts.
lead_paragraph: A Food and Drug Administration finding has given ammunition to consumer advocates who say the quality of generic drugs needs to be improved.

headline.seo: F.D.A. Increases Scrutiny of Some Generic Drugs
headline.main: An Increase in Scrutiny for Generics
headline.print_headline: An Increase In Scrutiny For Generics
